      • StringTransition

        public StringTransition(java.lang.String oldString,
                        java.lang.String newString,
                        Range range,
                        boolean preTransition)
        If preTransition is true, it means that the range we are giving is of the changes given from the perspective of the original tags. On the other hand, if preTransition is false, it means that the range we are getting is of the changes given from the perspective of the changed tags.
